Quote:  Tangiwai is clear like glass, and ranges from olive-gree to bluish green.  Most tangiwai is sourced from two isolated areas at Piopiotahi (Milford Sound).  Koko-tangiwai, the longer name for this stone, referes to a deep sorrow that is never completely healed.
